4 (2) The office of motor vehicles shall do both of the following:
5 (a)(i) Permit an inmate to use a copy of his birth certificate along with his
6 master prison record issued by the department as a valid form of photo identification
7 in order to obtain a special identification card.
8 (ii) For the purposes of this Subsection, "master prison record" means a
9 detailed calculation, maintained by the department, of the prison sentence of an
10 inmate that determines his release date and includes credit for time served, good
11 behavior, and program participation.
12 (b) Determine and assess a reasonable fee for the issuance of a special
13 identification card.
14 (3) A special identification card issued with a master prison record to an
15 inmate is nonrenewable, nontransferable, and is valid for a period of six years from
16 the month of issuance.
17 (4) The department may utilize any available funds, including but not limited
18 to inmate trust funds, existing department funds, and donations to cover the costs
19 associated with the implementation and administration of this Section and the
20 purchase of special identification cards.
21 C. The provisions of this Section apply only to inmates who receive a special
22 identification card pursuant to R.S. 40:1321, who are in the physical custody and
23 control of the department, and who are housed in a state correctional facility.
24 D. For the purposes of assisting an inmate with obtaining post-release
25 employment, the department shall provide an inmate with all of the following:
26 (1) A copy of the educational and vocational training credentials or
27 certifications of the inmate earned during incarceration, if applicable.
28 (2) A copy of the work record of the inmate, if applicable.
29 (3) A copy of the birth certificate of the inmate, if obtainable.
